
Questions
	Is globalization environmentally sustainable?
	Does technology sometimes make it easier to be local?
	- open source tools are accessible, allow local content production
	- maybe can create more w/o leaving home

Benefits
	UN, agreements on environment
	Global voluntary projects like Linux

Dangers
	Reliance on resources from elsewhere e.g. power, food
	Lack of choice if unable to produce locally

	Escalation of power of corporations vs. publically controlled bodies

